Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.96,0:59:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I know somebody who's very demanding and\Ndisliked as a consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.64,0:59:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And she never expresses appreciation for\Nanything. You know, would you mind when
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.35,0:59:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you go to town getting me 52 pounds of\Npotatoes and hauling them home? And then
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.59,0:59:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,when you get them home, she doesn't even\Nsay, "Gee, thanks."
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.20,1:00:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, as time goes on, people\Nare less and less willing to do things
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.31,1:00:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,for her. So, a simple thank you makes a\Ntremendous difference. People say,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.24,1:00:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, that's just a being polite." No,\Nit's not being just being polite. It's
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.83,1:00:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,acknowledging the worth of other human\Nbeings in your world. Uh so, you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.00,1:00:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,appreciate and you give thanks.\Nuh love level 500 and over indic it's in
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.44,1:00:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,shows appreciation.\NLove is supportive. You know you mutual
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.88,1:00:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,support.\NLove is also forgiving. So if the world
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.24,1:00:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,makes the mistake, you're willing to\Nforgive it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.07,1:00:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If people make a mistake, you're willing\Nto forgive them. So the willingness to
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.44,1:00:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,forgive marks a truly spiritual person.\Nthe willingness to forgive to let
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.52,1:00:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,bygones be bygones.\NAnd uh I think the 12step group
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.04,1:01:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,emphasizes the same thing. Live one day\Nat a time and let bygones be bygones.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.52,1:01:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody did you a bad term the people\Nin the group will tell you, well that
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.59,1:01:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,was yesterday.\NThat was yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.16,1:01:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is also inclusive. It's not\Nexclusive.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.96,1:01:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also affectionate and it has to do\Nwith being cordial and gracious
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.88,1:01:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and gracious. So to be cordial and\Ngracious and acknowledge the
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.59,1:01:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,acknowledge other people and the gift of\Ntheir presence. When you say thank you,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.96,1:01:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,people think that's just manners. It's\Nnot just manners. When you say thank
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.76,1:01:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you, you totally change the energy\Nfield. Uh you totally change the energy
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.16,1:02:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,field. You become uplifting. So\Npeople above 200 are supporting all of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.40,1:02:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,life and below 200 they are dragging\Ndown on it. So when you're
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.04,1:02:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,up uplifting, you are adding to the\Nenergy field of all of life and
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.64,1:02:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,especially of human life.\NUh love is also heart it's called
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.52,1:02:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,heartfelt and nurturing.\NLove is also understanding.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.83,1:02:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's protective.\NIt's dedicated to goodness. It's
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.04,1:02:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,dedicated to purity.\NIt's dedicated to giving to others.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:38.96,1:02:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is generous.\NLove is also capable of sharing.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.72,1:02:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also nonlinear.\NIt's holistic. It arises from the heart.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.16,1:03:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In lovingness, we join with other and we\Ndiffuse that love and set it up around
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.52,1:03:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,us. It's a way of being aligned. It's\Nalso humbling.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.04,1:03:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,One is humble and not prideful in\Nlovingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.35,1:03:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and we express our gratitude and when we\Ndo that there's completion. When you
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.96,1:03:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,express your gratitude and say thank you\Nthat completes the transaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.24,1:03:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So the failure to say thank you means\Nrejecting the other person instead of
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.76,1:03:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,accepting\Ntheir donation of love. There's a
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.31,1:03:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,certain sweetness to love. Love has a\Ncertain
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.72,1:03:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,capacity to attract affection. Yes.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.40,1:03:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,\Nhow do you get in there?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.07,1:03:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the sheep in wolf's clothing.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.64,1:04:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When when do we take a break?\N>> Um,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.07,1:04:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in about three minutes.\N>> Oh, okay. All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.79,1:04:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is important to know in today's\Nworld. We haven't gotten around to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.59,1:04:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,today's world yet.\NUh this is important to know because
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.00,1:04:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,uh one of the ways uh negativity\Nu
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.92,1:04:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to prevail uh how it gets such a\Nhold in life is because it misrepresents
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.68,1:04:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,itself\Nas a sheep. Uh the sheep don't bother
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.59,1:04:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,about us. We're just a happy religion.\NYeah. Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.24,1:04:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,until you hear the gunfire.\NThank you for all those love fellas.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.24,1:05:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nwe this is our friend and this is a good
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.96,1:05:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,one to keep in mind because when we get\Nto talking about today's world we are
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.24,1:05:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be\Nindirectly and unconsciously referring
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.28,1:05:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to situations that today prevail.\NWe're just innocent dogooders. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.92,1:05:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Put away the machine guns and\NI can believe you even better.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.31,1:05:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what do we do now?\N>> Well, I don't know. Can you turn me on?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.31,1:05:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Turn me on.\NYou turn me on, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.16,1:05:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You got to put a dime in the corner of\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.03,1:05:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Right. All right. I have I have to do\Nthis announcement. All right. Um, we're
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.52,1:05:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,going to take a quick break and we'll\Nsee you back here in about 15 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.00,1:06:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,How many\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.52,1:06:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.31,1:06:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And now\NI don't know what happens next, but
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.40,1:06:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll let us know.\NWhat do we do next, sweetheart?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.28,1:06:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Continue the lecture.\N>> Continue the lecture.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.59,1:07:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yep.\N>> She's my living breathing teleprompter.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.59,1:07:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Beats Obama's hands down.\NShe knows what's going on all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.76,1:07:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual survival in today's world.\NUhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.68,1:07:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The realities of the levels of\Nconsciousness. Reality is a subjective
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.28,1:07:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,mental presumption.\NWow.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.92,1:07:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is a presumption.\NYou ever think of that? You presume that
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.96,1:07:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're seeing is real,\Nbut you could be a lunatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.28,1:07:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In which case, nothing that you're\Nlooking at is real? You made it all up.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.55,1:07:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, is reality a subjective\Nmental presumption?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.68,1:08:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NReality linear versus nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.64,1:08:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,linear versus nonlinear.\NWhat does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.00,1:08:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Logical or not logical?\NWell, you notice the field of
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.56,1:08:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness is neither logical\Nnor is it non-logical. It just does not
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.40,1:08:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,address\Nuh the problem at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.79,1:08:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,One just experiences what you experience\Nand making a conclusion about it
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.15,1:08:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,requires\Nuh thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.92,1:08:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness itself is not the same as\Nthinkingness. Thinkingness is something
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.92,1:08:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,else. Again\Nuh so re reality is a subjective mental
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.92,1:08:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,presumption. We presume that what we see\Nis what is what really is.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.71,1:09:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh reality is one thing, truth is\Nanother.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.79,1:09:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Existentially\Nis the me real.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.92,1:09:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You presume you're real, but are you?\NYou never worried about that before.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.75,1:09:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good. Now there's something new to\Nworry about.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.12,1:09:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the me just imagine my imagination?\NThere are levels of consciousness where
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.75,1:09:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that really becomes a a problem.\NUh is there actually a me or is that
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.08,1:09:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,just some kind of a delusion?\NAnd what what is this I everything that
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.27,1:09:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I call I?\NWhy do you call it me or I in the first
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.67,1:09:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,place?\NWell, is the eye that which witnesses
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.96,1:10:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the world?\NIs the eye that which experiences the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.52,1:10:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,world\Nis the eye that which makes choices
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.52,1:10:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with the human will and\Nrelition.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.12,1:10:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's the I as a social\Npersonhood.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.67,1:10:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,People say you are you are what?\NThen there is I as my feelings. Am I my
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.96,1:10:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,feelings\Nor am I my thoughts?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.64,1:10:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How do I know that I even am?\NHow do you know that you are?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.08,1:10:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I know I am because I think and\Nbecause I feel
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.23,1:10:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and because other people seem to think\Nthat I am.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.04,1:10:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's reassuring.\NWalk in a room. When people say hello,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.04,1:10:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you say, "Oh, boy."\NWhat a relief. I wasn't sure if I was or
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.96,1:11:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,not.\NIs the real self just a blank screen on
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.96,1:11:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,which everything is reflected?\Nis the real self the content or the
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.44,1:11:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,context\Ndeart's proposition
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.52,1:11:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is reality\Nrest internal that is the way I
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.84,1:11:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,experience thing or is it rest external\Ndeart differentiated between
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.76,1:11:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the world as I experience it versus the\Nworld as it is I may experience it as
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.36,1:11:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,safe and it could be quite dangerous or\Nvice versa.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.84,1:11:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So the self knows\Nfrom one moment to next. Uh the mind
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.23,1:11:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks.\NSo thinkingness is one thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.88,1:12:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Experiencing reality is another.\NNone of these things become very
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.92,1:12:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,important unless one is seeking\Nenlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.84,1:12:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you seek enlightenment that\Nyou're letting go many of the things
Dialogue: 0,1:12:09.44,1:12:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that the world presumes presumes are\Nnecessary
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.71,1:12:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and and you let them go.\NUh and one thing you let go of is the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.04,1:12:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,mind's thinking.\NTherefore, if you can't think anymore,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:27.84,1:12:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you're only left with knowing.\NHow do you know without thinking? Well,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.04,1:12:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you discover that you you know without\Nthinking all the time and that thinking
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.15,1:12:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is just added as a frill.\NThinking is a frill and an
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.60,1:12:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,entertainment.\NCan you get along without thinking?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.67,1:12:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\NI'm not going to think about anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.92,1:13:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I should have thought\Nthere is a chair there. Well, I don't
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.56,1:13:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,think about the chair, but I know I know\Nit's there. So, most of real knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.60,1:13:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,goes on\Nuh without thinkingness. Thinkingness is
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.40,1:13:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,something we add. The human adds\Nthinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.12,1:13:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal knows without thinking. It\Nknows
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.96,1:13:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,a friend from foe.\NThe dog's hackles goes up if it's foe
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.00,1:13:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and its tail wags if it's friend. So the\Ndog doesn't have to think about it. It
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.36,1:13:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,just knows right off the bat who is a\Nfriend and who's a burglar.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.15,1:13:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A burglar. That's such a funny term, a\Nburglar. Isn't it funny? What does a
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.08,1:14:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,burglar do? be burgles.\NYou could go to burglar school.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.76,1:14:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,They do that in jail.\NPrisons are really burglar schools
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.44,1:14:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in which they trade information so\Nthey're better at it next time.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.44,1:14:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw a movie the other night about it.\Na true a true case of a guy really
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.36,1:14:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,learned how to rob banks. Uh he had an\Nexcellent technique. He was so good at
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.32,1:14:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it. He couldn't stop robbing banks. He\Nrobbed 12 in a row before uh the banking
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.56,1:14:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,system got became aware of his existence\Nand they put a loaded uh loaded money
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.40,1:14:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that so if um in a bank teller a guy\Nholds a gun on her and says give me your
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.80,1:14:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,money. She gives him this pack of bills.\NAnd this pack of bills, if he takes
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.76,1:14:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that, it's got a timer on it. And the\Ntimer is released and suddenly red ink
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.64,1:15:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,squirts out all over. And the cops have\Nno problem finding them. So,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.48,1:15:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, it's best not the burgl\Nis reality. Therefore, the essence or
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.23,1:15:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the appearance of a thing?\NUh remember Alice in Wonderland? So
Dialogue: 0,1:15:19.92,1:15:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that's all based on opinion uh opinion\Nvirtual reality of the media.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.28,1:15:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is a projection and illusion.\NThe sense of reality
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.71,1:15:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs in one 10,000th of a second.\NWithin one 10,000th of a second, your
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.19,1:15:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,mind is already made up, is already\Naware of whether it's an illusion or a
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.48,1:15:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,reality.\NUhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.15,1:15:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So the mind by itself really is without\Na compass. The mind has no capacity to
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.80,1:16:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,tell truth from falsehood.\NUhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.44,1:16:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In the United States, 55% of the people\Nare unable to differentiate reality from
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.44,1:16:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,illusion.\NWhat do you know about that? 55%
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.23,1:16:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,can't tell reality from illusion. Is\Nthat a fact?
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.96,1:16:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,55% of the people in the United States\Ncannot tell reality from an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:25.19,1:16:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That explains the daily news.\NThat explains the daily news. Yeah. Uh
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.80,1:16:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind does not have a compass to tell\Nit. Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.04,1:16:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the system that we have evolved of how\Nto tell truth from falsehood is of great
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.64,1:16:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,very great pragmatic value.\NUh in the United States, belief systems
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.60,1:17:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to get politicized. Not only the\NUnited States, but all around the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.64,1:17:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And\Nnarcissism is the presumption that the
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.96,1:17:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,way I look at it is correct and the way\Nyou look at it is is incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.60,1:17:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NIndoctrination, we find trumps reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.44,1:17:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, if we indoctrinate\Npeople, they lose the capacity to
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.76,1:17:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,discern reality.\NIndoctrination univer university is a
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.19,1:17:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,book called indoctrination that\Ndocuments how
Dialogue: 0,1:17:35.36,1:17:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,uh how it how it's brought about.\NTherefore, we could say all information
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.36,1:17:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is presumptive.\NIt's best to send your kids to Yavapai
